page.title: 05HOUSES IN BEAULIEU
page.content: There was only one house that we could find with a date on it and it was Norris's shop. The date was 1876, one hundred and nine years old.There was also a builders with some weird looking initials they were {B.B ,W.H and {M.O}. Most houses in Beaulieu are private. The one road we walked down had eleven private houses .The houses had funny names like Pepperbox house, Old Bank house ,Morris house and Warners house. There is one shop called Secrets of the Forest. It was named after a book. They asked the lady who wrote the book if they could call it after the book. The lady agreed and from that day she has made little mice and sent them to the shop from Wales where she lives.
